<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp14942656">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp38118720">
<p id="fs-idp23217968">Explain how ammonia can function both as a Br&#248;nsted base and as a Lewis base.</p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idp78810976">
<p id="fs-idp95893216">Ammonia acts as a Br&#248;nsted base because it readily accepts protons and as a Lewis base in that it has an electron pair to donate.<span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
Br&#248;nsted base: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>NH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mo>+</mo></msup><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo stretchy="false">&#10230;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msub><mrow><mtext>NH</mtext></mrow><mn>4</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mtext>O</mtext></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>NH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mo>+</mo></msup><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo stretchy="false">&#10230;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msub><mrow><mtext>NH</mtext></mrow><mn>4</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mtext>O</mtext></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math><span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
Lewis base: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>2NH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>Ag</mtext></mrow><mo>+</mo></msup><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo stretchy="false">&#10230;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>[H</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mtext>N</mtext><mo>&#8722;</mo><mtext>Ag</mtext><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>NH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>2NH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>Ag</mtext></mrow><mo>+</mo></msup><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo stretchy="false">&#10230;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>[H</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mtext>N</mtext><mo>&#8722;</mo><mtext>Ag</mtext><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>NH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
